## 2. Rollback Decision Criteria

Initiate rollback **immediately** if any of the following are observed post-deployment:

### Automatic Triggers (no discussion needed — rollback immediately)
- [ ] Application is completely down / unreachable
- [ ] Health endpoint returns non-200 for > 2 minutes
- [ ] Data corruption detected
- [ ] Security breach detected

### Escalation Triggers (consult Release Manager before rolling back)
- [ ] Error rate exceeds `[TO BE FILLED]`% for > 5 minutes
- [ ] Critical user flow failure (e.g. login, payments, core feature)
- [ ] P0/P1 incident raised within 30 minutes of deployment
- [ ] SLA breach imminent

### Do NOT Rollback If
- Minor cosmetic issues that can be hotfixed
- Non-critical feature degradation that does not affect core flows
- Issue already being resolved by a forward fix (confirm with Release Manager)

